body_html:
@dandelionmane To be honest, I have no idea how to activate the Chrome debugger console. Can you explain it to me? If you mean the console, I can open with [Ctrl]+[Shift]+J, there is nothing inside. Do I need to activate any special mode?

In the very first post, I paste the output of the terminal, when I start tensorboard with --inspect argument. Here you can see, that the graph is found by tensorboard inside the event file.

@dandelionmane To be honest, I have no idea how to activate the Chrome debugger console. Can you explain it to me? If you mean the console, I can open with [Ctrl]+[Shift]+J, there is nothing inside. Do I need to activate any special mode? 

In the very first post, I paste the output of the terminal, when I start tensorboard with `--inspect` argument. Here you can see, that the graph is found by tensorboard inside the event file.
